President Obama has nominated Judge Denny Chin for the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit and Judge O. Rogeriee Thompson for the United States Court of Appeals for the First Circuit. Judge Chin currently serves as a U.S. District Court Judge for the Southern District of New York, while Judge Thompson is an Associate Justice on the Rhode Island Superior Court. President Obama praised both judges for their dedication to public service and expressed confidence in their ability to serve on the appellate courts. Judge Chin, who was born in Hong Kong and raised in New York City, has a background in labor and employment law and has been an Adjunct Professor at Fordham University School of Law. Judge Thompson, who was born and raised in South Carolina, has experience in family law, civil rights, and Native American law. She has served on the Rhode Island District Court and the Rhode Island Superior Court, where she has chaired the Court's Ad Hoc Task Force on Limited English Speaking Litigants.